dlier's Advice for Irish Catholic Girls / rHernadi, Liz Szabo -- t16. John Humphrey Noyes, the Oneida Community, and Male Continence / rMcClymond, Michael J. -- t17. Is Life Worth Living? / rCroce, Paul Jerome -- t18. In His Steps: A Social Gospel Novel / rOlson, Janet C. -- tHealing: Health, Happiness, and the Miraculous -- t19. The Spiritual Meanings of Illness in Eighteenth-Century New England / rMinkema, Kenneth Ρ. -- t20. Supernaturalism and Healing in the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints / rUnderwood, Grant -- t21. Christian Physiology and Diet Reform / rGardella, Peter -- t22. Sickness, Death, and Illusion in Christian Science / rPrentiss, Craig R. -- t23. The Miracles of St. Anthony of Padua / rMeagher, Timothy J. -- tImagining: The Unseen World -- t24. The Life and Death of Mother Marie de Saint Joseph / rBoss, Julia -- t25. Possession, Witchcraft, and the Demonic in Puritan Religious Culture / rMinkema, Kenneth Ρ. -- t26. Speech of Sose-Há-Wä and the Code of Handsome Lake / rDennis, Matthew -- t27. A Methodist Dream of Heaven and Homeland / rSchneider, A. Gregory -- t28. African-American Vision Stories / rReis, Elizabeth -- tPersuading: Witnessing, Controversies, and Polemics -- t29. Native American Visionary Experience and Christian Missions / rMcNally, Michael D. -- t30. American Anti-Catholic Pornography / rGardella, Peter -- t31. The Christian Doctrine of Slavery / rHarvey, Paul -- t32. Trance Lecturers in Antebellum America / rBraude, Ann -- t33. The Cremation versus Burial Debate / rProthero, Stephen -- tIndex  aReligions of the United States in Practice is a rich anthology of primary sources with accompanying essays that examines religious behavior in America. From praying in an early American synagogue to performing Mormon healing rituals to debating cremation, Volume 1 explores faith through action from Colonial times through the nineteenth century. The documents and essays consider the religious practices of average people--praying, singing, healing, teaching, imagining, and persuading. Some documents are formal liturgies while other texts describe more spontaneous religious actions. Because religious practices also take place in the imagination, dreams, visions, and fictional accounts are also included. Accompanying each primary document is an essay that sets the religious practice in its historical and theological context--making this volume ideal for classroom use and accessible to any reader. The introductory essays explain the various meanings of religious practices as lived out in churches and synagogues, in parlors and fields, beside rivers, on lecture platforms, and in the streets. Religions of the United States in Practice offers a sampling of religious perspectives in order to approximate the living texture of popular religious thought and practice in the United States. The history of religion in America is more than the story of institutions and famous people. This anthology presents a more nuanced story composed of the everyday actions and thoughts of lay men and women.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Mai 2019) 7aRELIGION / History.2bisacsh1 aMcDannell, Colleen, eeditor.40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691188126zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780691188126.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG  aPDA9PRIN